President Joe Biden has nominated Jennifer Abruzzo as the General Counsel of the National Labor Relations Board (NLRB). Abruzzo, who has more than two decades of experience at the NLRB, will work to enforce U.S. labor laws and protect workers' rights. She will contribute to rebuilding America's middle class and promoting a stronger and more inclusive economy. The NLRB is an independent agency that focuses on advancing and protecting fair labor practices in the United States. Abruzzo currently serves as Special Counsel for Strategic Initiatives for the Communications Workers of America.